2026-07-10T05:20:43.8758961Z               "message": "Address review findings: SPF correctness, cache lifecycle, and API hardening\n\nCorrectness\n- SPF: bare `all` (implicit +all) is now scored Error instead of Pass; the\n  all-mechanism handling normalizes the qualifier rather than matching literal\n  \"+all\"/\"~all\"/etc. strings (SpfRecordCheck).\n- SPF: SpfExpansionCheck now derives severity from recorded Errors/Warnings, so\n  include:/redirect= targets with no SPF record (PermErrors) no longer report Pass.\n- SPF: SpfExpansionCheck reads the per-validation CheckContext.QueryErrors bag\n  (populated via the AsyncLocal) instead of the shared Dns.QueryErrors, which is\n  empty under the web server — fixes transient-vs-permanent misclassification.\n- DNSSEC: removed dead DS-KeyTag cross-reference block (condition was always false).\n\nPerformance / caching\n- DnsResolverService reuses one LookupClient per target server IP instead of\n  allocating a fresh client on every uncached server query (identical options).\n- Web ValidationTracker now evicts stuck Running jobs past a hard max age so they\n  can't accumulate.\n- Disk cache: DNS query/server-query entries carry their real fetch time through\n  ProbeCache (ExportTimed/Import-with-timestamp); merge-on-save honours it so a\n  re-fetched entry's TTL ages from its latest fetch while untouched imported\n  entries keep their original timestamp. Other caches unchanged.\n- CachedDnsResponse.Header no longer throws — it reconstructs a header from the\n  persisted RCODE so IsNxDomain and future callers work on reloaded responses.\n\nSecurity (web/API)\n- Debug proxy endpoint is unavailable whenever auth is disabled (admin-only,\n  auth-enabled only) so it can't be an open SSRF surface.\n- Auth-disabled instances refuse to start unless bound to loopback only.\n- Basic domain-format validation on both validate endpoints, closing the\n  unescaped-URL-interpolation vector (userinfo/path/port in the domain).\n- HTTPS certificate validation is ON by default for HTTP probes, with an explicit\n  ValidateHttpsCertificates=false opt-out for TLS-intercepting-proxy environments.\n- IssueToken response no longer echoes the stored token hash.\n- Documented root-token minimum-entropy requirement and the localhost/TLS options.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PD81wS9yngzumYcPpdYDsv",
2026-07-10T05:20:43.8769747Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-10T03:07:51Z",
