2026-07-10T05:20:43.8774723Z               "id": "2d353c8730055ea2ac38ac64f406f7442c44ffaa",
2026-07-10T05:20:43.8781355Z               "message": "Fix DKIM key-size accuracy, VMC CN parsing, IPv6 false-positives, and UI truncation\n\nSurfaced while reviewing a live cnn.com validation:\n\n- DKIM key size is now derived from the actual RSA modulus (RSA.KeySize) instead\n  of estimating from the base64 length of the SubjectPublicKeyInfo, which\n  overstated sizes by ~270 bits (reported 1024-bit keys as ~1296, 2048 as ~2352).\n  Falls back to the old length estimate, labelled approximate, only for keys that\n  can't be parsed as SPKI or PKCS#1. Shared by DkimSelectorsCheck and ArcCheck.\n- ExtractCn (VMC subject) now splits the DN respecting quoted RDN values and\n  backslash escapes, so CN=\"Cable News Network, Inc.\" is no longer truncated at\n  the internal comma.\n- IPv6-dependent checks (NS lame delegation, SOA serial consistency, SMTP IPv6\n  connectivity) detect whether the host has an outbound IPv6 route via a new\n  NetworkCapabilities helper. When it doesn't, IPv6 targets are skipped with a\n  clear note instead of being misreported as the target's unreachable/lame NS or\n  broken MX IPv6.\n- Web UI: warnings and errors are now rendered first and never truncated; only the\n  informational details are capped at 20. Previously the combined list was capped\n  with warnings/errors last, so a check with many detail lines (DKIM, blocklists)\n  could hide its actionable findings behind \"...and N more\".\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nClaude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01PD81wS9yngzumYcPpdYDsv",
2026-07-10T05:20:43.8786900Z               "timestamp": "2026-07-10T03:35:54Z",
